'''Geomelophagia''' is an unusual [[Pica (disorder)|pica]] (medical eating disorder) <ref>{{cite book |title= Handbook of Evidence-Based Practice in Clinical Psychology, Child and Adolescent Disorders |vauthors=Sturmey P, Hersen M |publisher= John Wiley & Sons |year= 2012  |page=304}} See [https://books.google.com/books?id=Gg8EjCzk1IQC&lpg=PA304&dq=pica%20geomelophagia&pg=PA304#v=snippet&q=geomelophagia&f=false]</ref> in [[iron-deficiency anemia]] and is characterized by abnormal ingestion of raw [[potato]]es.<ref>{{cite book |title= A Dictionary of Psychology |author= Coleman AM |publisher= Oxford University Press |year= 2015 |page= 576 }} See [https://books.google.com/books?id=zvlrBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA576&dq=pica+hyalophagia&hl=en&sa=X&ei=auncVO75EoKhyATiuIDYDQ&ved=0CCIQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=pica%20hyalophagia&f=false Google books link.]</ref><ref>{{cite journal|pmid=7148884|year=1982|last1=Johnson|first1=BE|last2=Stephens|first2=RL|title=Geomelophagia. An unusual pica in iron-deficiency anemia|volume=73|issue=6|pages=931–2|journal=The American Journal of Medicine|doi=10.1016/0002-9343(82)90802-6}}</ref>

