{{Infobox lake | name = Nøklevann | image = Nøklevann - 2012-08-12 at 13-28-36.jpg | caption = Nøklevann, seen from north | image_bathymetry = Nøklevann.svg | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Oslo]], [[Norway]] | coords = {{coord|59|52|31|N|10|52|37|E|region:NO-03_type:waterbody_source:kolossus-nowiki|display=title,inline}} | type = Natural lake | inflow = | outflow = [[Ljanselva]] | basin_countries = Norway | area = {{convert|0.63|km2|abbr=on}}<ref name="miljolare">[http://www.miljolare.no/data/ut/omrade/?o_id=916&full=1 Miljolare.no]</ref> | depth = | max-depth = {{convert|34|m|abbr=on}} | volume = <!-- {{convert|7.56|e6m3|acre.ft|abbr=on}}<ref name="miljolare" /> --> | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = {{convert|163|m|abbr=on}} | islands = | cities = | reference = }} [[File:Nøklevann dam 09-11-28.jpg|thumb|right|The [[Nøklevann Dam]] at [[Rustadsaga]].]] '''Nøklevann''' is a lake in [[Østmarka]] in [[Oslo]], Norway. It has a surface area of 0.8&nbsp;km², and is 163 meters above sea level. The lake drains through [[Ljanselva]] to [[Bunnefjorden]]. It is a former drinking water supply for Oslo.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Nøklevann |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor-last=Godal | editor-first=Anne Marit | editor-link=Anne Marit Godal |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |url=http://snl.no/Nøklevann |language=Norwegian|accessdate=21 November 2012}}</ref>
